  "name": "Kuznetsov 1994 tumor-immune QSP (HYPOTHESIS-TIER, NOT FOR PREDICTION)",
  "description": "Nondimensional tumor-immune predator-prey model: d(tumor)/dt = alpha*tumor*(1-beta*tumor) - (1+E)*effector*tumor; d(effector)/dt = s + rho*effector*tumor/(eta+tumor) - mu*effector*tumor - delta*effector. Reproduces immune control / tumor dormancy / immune escape QUALITATIVELY; an immunotherapy effect E (e.g. checkpoint blockade) augments the immune kill. HYPOTHESIS-TIER: ships tier D, non-predictive, because the quantitative validation to do otherwise honestly does not yet exist. Parameter values are the classic Kuznetsov 1994 nondimensional set (illustrative) and unverified.",
